Levpartflip¶

Wrapper for SAM Simulation Core model: cmod_levpartflip.cpp

Creating an Instance¶

There are three methods to create a new instance of a PySAM module. Using default populates the newclass’ attributes with default values specific to a config. Each technology-financialconfiguration corresponds to a SAM GUI configuration. Using new creates an instance with empty attributes. The wrap function allows compatibility with PySSC, for details, refer to PySSC.

Levpartflip model description

PPA leveraged partnership flip (with debt) financial model

PySAM.Levpartflip.default(config) → Levpartflip¶

Use financial config-specific default attributes config options:

  • “BiopowerLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “DSLFLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “DSPTLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “DishStirlingLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “EmpiricalTroughLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “FlatPlatePVLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “GenericCSPSystemLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “GenericSystemLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “GeothermalPowerLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “HighXConcentratingPVLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “MSLFLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “MSPTLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

  • “PVWattsLeveragedPartnershipFlip”

PySAM.Levpartflip.from_existing(data, optional config) → Levpartflip¶

Share underlying data with an existing PySAM class. If config provided, default attributes are loaded otherwise.

PySAM.Levpartflip.new() → Levpartflip¶
PySAM.Levpartflip.wrap(ssc_data_t) → Levpartflip¶

Use existing PySSC data

Warning

Do not call PySSC.data_free on the ssc_data_t provided to wrap

Functions¶

class PySAM.Levpartflip.Levpartflip¶

This class contains all the variable information for running a simulation. Variables are grouped together in the subclasses as properties. If property assignments are the wrong type, an error is thrown.

assign(dict) → None¶

Assign attributes from nested dictionary, except for Outputs

nested_dict = { 'Revenue': { var: val, ...}, ...}

execute(int verbosity) → None¶

Execute simulation with verbosity level 0 (default) or 1

export() → dict¶

Export attributes into nested dictionary

value(name, optional value) → Union[None, float, dict, sequence, str]¶

Get or set by name a value in any of the variable groups.
